<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,456,856]" pageId="8" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,456,482]" pageId="8" pageNumber="46">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[290,456,457,482]" class="Insecta" family="Fanniidae" genus="Fannia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis box="[290,456,457,482]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="46">Fannia pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[766,843,457,483]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="46">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wendt" box="[859,1170,457,483]" pageId="8" pageNumber="46" refString="Wendt, L. D. &amp; Carvalho, C. J. B. de (2009) Taxonomia de Fanniidae (Diptera) do sul do Brasil - II: novas especies e chaves de identificacao de Fannia Robineau-Desvoidy. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 53, 171 - 206." type="journal article" year="2009">
Wendt &amp; Carvalho 
<number box="[1106,1170,457,483]" pageId="8" pageNumber="46" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and in several other countries in the New World, Africa and the Mediterranean (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[909,1157,494,520]" pageId="8" pageNumber="46" refString="Carvalho, C. J. B de, Pont, A. C., Couri, M. S. &amp; Pamplona, D (2003) A catalogue of the Fanniidae (Diptera) of the Neotropical Region. Zootaxa, 219, 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="2003">
Carvalho 
<emphasis box="[1025,1077,494,519]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[1093,1157,494,520]" pageId="8" pageNumber="46" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However, this species was not recorded for the northern region of 
<collectingCountry box="[684,758,531,557]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="46">Brazil</collectingCountry>
until now. In the collections examined, male specimens from the state of Pará were found, hence the distribution of 
<emphasis box="[851,939,569,594]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="46">F. p u s i o</emphasis>
is expanded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
